This page collects information about non-Motorola Linux-based mobile phones. This is useful as many parts of OpenEZX are probably usable for other phones, too (and vice versa).

== LiMo Foundation ==
The [http://www.limofoundation.org LiMo Foundation] is an industry committee tasked with creating a Linux-based mobile OS and application stack with a unified API. Its [http://www.limofoundation.org/current-members/index.php members] include Motorola, Vodafone, LG, Samsung, and Nokia (through Trolltech).  The beta API was released Feb 2008 to members, and is due for public release H2/2008 with the first phones Q4/2008.  The following LiMo-based phones were [http://www.limofoundation.org/press-releases/limo-press-releases/limo-foundation-unveils-first-limo-handsets.html announced] Feb 2008 at Mobile World Congress in Spain.


